snippet.textDisplay: Random fun fact... Colonel Sanders hated the chicken sold by KFC. After it went and became a huge corporation and he went from being the owner to just a spokesperson, they changed the original recipe he used so they could make their food more, shall we say, mass produced. And he fuckin hated the changes they made to it, to the point that when interviewed by news outlets he would outright call the food terrible. He would even go so far as to show up at random KFC restaurants and walk into the kitchen and teach the staff how to cook it The REAL WAY. Ans according to people who had gotten to eat the original recipe chicken as originally made by Sanders, it was much, MUCH, better than what they sell today. So if you are thinking KFC's sandwich is great now, imagine how much better it would have been if they actually used the True Original Recipe for the chicken.

snippet.textDisplay: Chick-fil-A is the one people go crazy for not Popeyes. Honestly, I've heard people say nobody gets stabbed for Chick-fil-A but I've never seen a Popeye's outside a slum neighborhood you aren't likely to get stabbed in anyway, and I've never seen a Chick-fil-A by the slums, so I always assumed it was more about that than food quality. Growing up, Popeye's would have been my second fav if not for 2 things: It was infamous in my hometown for serving maggots one season (turned people off from trying it) and it was dangerous to go into the hoods where Popeye's were... you could get stabbed just for being an outsider in the wrong hood, so I never really went to Popeye's much for safety reasons (can still go to the drive-thru on road trips). Granted, I have NOT been to every town or city in America, so these observations may be regional... also possibly regional, I've never had a piece of chicken from Chick-fil-A that wasn't plump, juicy, fresh, and so high quality that you almost thought it should still be cluckin'. The quality rivals the best chicken cuts at the poultry counter... Every time I have had chick sandwiches from every other place they are at best about 10% the food quality of Chick-fil-A, smashed, processed, and unrecognizable as chicken. The low quality I hear others describing from Chick-fil-A would literally get you fired from Chick-fil-A where I come from, no exaggeration. So, again, these being franchises usually, I think it's regional. Five guys was good in my hometown. I moved to the opposite coast and it's crap. So, again, the region makes a difference.
